import { Component } from '@angular/core'; import { ThemeService } from '../theme.service'; @Component({ selector: 'app-home', templateUrl: './home.component.html', styleUrls: ['./home.component.scss'] }) export class HomeComponent { currentTheme: string; constructor(private themeService: ThemeService){} ngOnInit(): void { this.themeService.currentTheme$.subscribe(theme => { this.currentTheme = theme; // Perform any necessary actions based on the updated theme }); } }

Anas Malvat

Hi 👋, I'm Anas, a 🎓 Masters in Applied Computer Science graduate from 🏫 Dalhousie University. I have a strong passion for 💻 Backend Development, Cloud Technologies, 🚀DevOps, and Front-End development with Angular and React. I am also a AWS Certified Solutions Architect. During my co-op experience at Canada Revenue Agency, I gained valuable knowledge in technologies such as Jenkins, OpenShift, Java, Angular, and gRPC. In addition, I am a co-founder of Dalhousie Computer Science Leaders 🌟, where we help students prepare for coding interviews and enhance their problem-solving skills. When I have free time, you can find me solving coding problems on GeeksForGeeks, 💪 working out, or immersing myself in 📚 books.
